<br>
Shrinking:  Everyone needs to get shrunk for indoor raids.  That means casters too.  The only people who shouldn't be shrunk are the chanters and possibly the puller.  It's very hard to run around and get targets on adds to slow them when I'm backed into a corner by two full sized wizards.  When I say in guildchat &quot;invite me for shrink,&quot; make a spot in your group ASAP and invite me to get shrunk.  Don't wait 15 minutes till I've joined my full time group and changed my spells around, forcing me to drop group again and change spells.<br>
<br>
Buffs:  When I say in guildchat &quot;send me tells for xx buff,&quot; PLEASE check your buffs to make sure you either don't have or don't need it, and send me tells appropriately.  For group buffs, if I say &quot;group leaders send me a tell for xx,&quot; if you are a group leader, PLEASE send me a tell; don't make me spam.  Example, the other night for lord bob I was the only shaman there.  I asked in chat for group leaders to send me a tell so I could group agility everyone.  There were at least four groups there, and I got two tells.  <br>
<br>
I really hate spamming guildchat with &quot;send me tells, etc&quot; because people aren't paying attention, and I know that not everyone is buffed.  If the raid buffers are asking for tells, check your buffs to make sure you have everything you need.<br>
<br>
Also.... if you die, get dispelled, whatever and lose your buffs, send a tell to whomever you need.  Sometimes it can be a bit hard to keep track of who needs what and when if there are a lot of people at a raid all milling around.<br>
<br>
Please keep this stuff in mind when we raid.  Buffing is a big part of a shaman's job, and I like to get it done as quickly as possible so the raid can progress smoothly and without delay.  Things that make me less efficient at my job get on my nerves a bit. =)  I'm sure other buffers will agree.<br>
<br>
